{
  "text": "Maassen et al. reported a case of TAE for atonic uterus after normal delivery. There was persistent bleeding after TAE therefore re-TAE was performed. Gelatin sponges were injected into both internal iliac arteries, however, the woman continued to bleed and an emergency hysterectomy was required. The reason of persistent bleeding was continued blood supply from the ovarian arteries to the uterus. In this case, it was important to check the accessory blood supply [CITATION_1] .",
